        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 17 at 6:37AM EDT until May 17 at 7:00AM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 637 AM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 12 miles northwest
of Spartanburg, or near Lake Bowen, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind
damage to trees and power lines.

Locations impacted include...
Cliffside, Cowpens National Battlefield, Lake Bowen, Chesnee, Harris,
Spartanburg, Inman, Mayo, USC Upstate, and Green Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
